\begin_layout Standard
The last ingredient of a probability space is a probability measure 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{P}:\mathcal{F}\rightarrow[0,1]$
\end_inset

 that assigns to each event a real number in the closed interval 
\begin_inset Formula $[0,1]$
\end_inset

 subject to the following conditions: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{P}(\Omega)=1$
\end_inset

, and 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
For any collection of pairwise disjoint events 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{i}$
\end_inset

, we have 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{P}(\bigcup_{i}A_{i})=\Sigma_{i}~\mathbb{P}(A_{i})$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

